1937;;The Devil's Playground;;American;;Erle C. Kenton;;Dolores del Río, Richard Dix, Ward Bond;;drama;;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Devil%27s_Playground_(1937_film);;Submarine officers Dorgan (Richard Dix) and Mason (Chester Morris) battle on land for the affections of dance-hall girl Carmen (Dolores del Río). She marries Dorgan but makes a play for Mason when her husband is on duty. The romantic rivalry is forgotten when Dorgan must rescue Mason and his crew from a sunken sub.[1]